+# CareOn — M1 plan (shell-only consumer migration)
+
+**Status:** Plan — **read-only / awaiting approval**. No code changes, no migration performed.
+**Date:** 2026-06-18
+**Scope:** M1 of the convergence migration (decision doc §5) — **only** the two shell-only consumers of `CareCommandPrimitives` that import nothing but `CareCommandShell`:
+- `client/src/components/care/PlacementPage.tsx`
+- `client/src/components/care/AccessDeniedPage.tsx`
+
+**Out of scope:** all other consumers; any worklist/metric migration; pagination; `CareWorkRow`; A status change/removal; backend/router/API; broad cleanup. M1 does **not** touch `CareCommandPrimitives` itself.
+
+---
+
+## 0. Why these two first
+
+Per the consumer heatmap they import **only** `CareCommandShell` (1 export each) — the smallest blast radius — and exercise the new B path end-to-end before any worklist page. M1 depends on no M0 deliverable (these pages use the page shell, not the metric card), so M1 may proceed independently once approved.
+
+---
+
+## 1. Shared mapping — `CareCommandShell` (A) → `CarePageScaffold` + canonical header (B)
+
+`CareCommandShell({ title, subtitle?, lastUpdatedLabel?, onRefresh?, actions?, children, testId? })` renders: `h1.care-text-title` + optional subtitle + an actions/refresh row, then `children`.
+
+`CarePageScaffold({ archetype, title, subtitle?, titleClassName?, actions?, metric?, children, testId? })` renders the header via `CareUnifiedHeader` (`data-testid="care-page-header"`) then content (`data-testid="care-page-content"`), in the canonical order header → dominant → KPI → filters → content → insights.
+
+| `CareCommandShell` prop | Target in `CarePageScaffold` | Note |
+|---|---|---|
+| `title` (ReactNode) | `title` | Direct 1:1 |
+| `subtitle?` (string) | `subtitle?` | Direct 1:1 |
+| `actions?` | `actions?` | Direct 1:1 |
+| `children` | `children` | Direct 1:1 (lands in `care-page-content`) |
+| `lastUpdatedLabel?` / `onRefresh?` | — (no built-in) | **Neither page uses these** → no parity gap. (If ever needed, render in `actions` or add to the header — out of M1 scope.) |
+| `testId?` | `testId?` | Direct 1:1 |
+| *(new required)* | `archetype` | **Must be chosen per page** — see §4 design input |
+
+A lighter alternative (header only, no scaffold slots) is `CareUnifiedHeader`/`PageHeader` + a plain content `div`. **Recommendation:** use `CarePageScaffold` so both pages declare an archetype and inherit the canonical layout (consistent with the archetype map). Decide per §4.
+
+---
+
+## 2. Page — `PlacementPage.tsx`
+
+- **Current A imports:** `import { CareCommandShell } from "./CareCommandPrimitives";` (line 15). Used **twice** (two render branches, ~lines 224 and 266). Also uses B's `LoadingState`/`ErrorState`/`EmptyState`/`PrimaryActionButton` for other branches (already canonical — untouched).
+- **Usage shape:** `<CareCommandShell title={<JSX>} actions={<PrimaryActionButton…/>}>…children…</CareCommandShell>`. No `onRefresh`/`lastUpdatedLabel`/`subtitle` used.
+- **Target mapping:** replace both `CareCommandShell` blocks with `CarePageScaffold archetype="detail" title={…} actions={…}>…</CarePageScaffold>` (archetype = **Detail Workspace**, per `CAREON_SCREEN_ARCHETYPE_MAP.md`: "Plaatsingsbevestiging | PlacementPage"). Import `CarePageScaffold` from the `CareDesignPrimitives` barrel.
+- **Prop/content/layout differences:** title/actions/children map 1:1. Header markup differs (CareCommandShell `h1` vs CareUnifiedHeader) → minor visual shift in header spacing/typography; scaffold wraps content in `care-page-content` and adds `data-care-page-archetype="detail"`. No content reflow expected because the page already supplies its own body.
+- **Risk of visual/behaviour change:** **Low–Medium.** Behaviour identical (no refresh/interaction in the shell). Visual: header band may shift slightly (token-strict) — acceptable per **D4** (behaviour/info/a11y/responsive parity required; pixel parity not). Two call-sites → migrate both in the same PR.
+- **Existing tests:** `client/src/components/care/PlacementPage.test.tsx` exists (safety net). Placement path also exercised indirectly by golden-path e2e.
+- **Additional tests needed:** update/confirm `PlacementPage.test.tsx` still passes; add an assertion that the page renders the canonical header hook (`data-testid="care-page-header"`) and content (`care-page-content`) instead of the old shell. Keep assertions behaviour-focused (title text, actions present), not markup-brittle.
+- **Visual-regression baseline:** capture before/after Playwright screenshots of `/plaatsingen` placement-confirmation view; update the visual baseline with design sign-off (expected token-strict header shift).
+- **Rollback:** revert the M1 PR (single commit) — restores the `CareCommandShell` import + two blocks; no other file affected.
+
+## 3. Page — `AccessDeniedPage.tsx` (88 lines)
+
+- **Current A imports:** `import { CareCommandShell } from "./CareCommandPrimitives";` (line 6). Used once: `<CareCommandShell title={copy.title}>…children (a content block, incl. an inner title)…</CareCommandShell>`. Only `title` + `children`.
+- **Target mapping:** `<CarePageScaffold archetype="support" title={copy.title}>…</CarePageScaffold>` (archetype = **Support/Evidence**, the natural fit for a peripheral access-denied surface; not yet in the archetype map → see §4).
+- **Prop/content/layout differences:** title/children 1:1; no actions/subtitle/refresh. Trivial.
+- **Risk of visual/behaviour change:** **Low.** Static page, no interaction; only header rendering differs slightly.
+- **Existing tests:** none found (no dedicated test/story).
+- **Additional tests needed:** add a small `AccessDeniedPage.test.tsx` (render → title text present, content present, canonical header hook present). This both covers the migration and closes a coverage gap.
+- **Visual-regression baseline:** capture `/geen-toegang` screenshot; set baseline (first-time).
+- **Rollback:** revert the M1 PR; single file.
+
+---
+
+## 4. Design input required before coding M1
+
+1. **Scaffold vs header-only:** confirm using `CarePageScaffold` (archetype-declaring) over a bare `CareUnifiedHeader`. (Recommended: scaffold.)
+2. **Archetype tokens:** confirm `PlacementPage` → `archetype="detail"` and `AccessDeniedPage` → `archetype="support"` (verify exact `CarePageArchetype` token strings in `CarePageScaffold.tsx`; add `AccessDeniedPage` to `CAREON_SCREEN_ARCHETYPE_MAP.md` as Support in the same PR).
+3. **Visual baseline acceptance:** agree that the token-strict header shift is an accepted baseline update (D4), not a regression.
+
+---
+
+## 5. Cross-cutting
+
+- **Sequence:** `AccessDeniedPage` first (trivial, closes a test gap, lowest risk), then `PlacementPage` (two call-sites, has a unit test). One page per PR, or both in one small PR — recommend **one PR per page** for clean rollback.
+- **Guards interaction:** after migration, neither page imports `CareCommandShell`; once **all** A consumers are gone (much later), the PR-D forbidden-import guard can enforce A as Deprecated. M1 alone does **not** change A's status (still `Needs consolidation`).
+- **No new A imports**, no `CareCommandPrimitives` edits, no other pages touched.
+
+## 6. Exit criteria (per page)
+
+1. The page imports the shell from the `CareDesignPrimitives` barrel (`CarePageScaffold`) and **no longer** imports `CareCommandShell` from `CareCommandPrimitives`.
+2. `tsc --noEmit`, Vitest, `check:careon-design`, diff-scoped token-governance, terminology guard, frontend build, Storybook build (if in CI), UI Verification, Platform Guardrails — all green.
+3. Behaviour/info/a11y/responsive parity verified; visual baseline updated with design sign-off (D4).
+4. Unit test present and green (`PlacementPage.test.tsx` updated; new `AccessDeniedPage.test.tsx`).
+5. Diff limited to the single page file (+ its test, + the archetype-map doc line for AccessDenied); zero other consumers/pages changed; A unchanged.
+
+No code or migration is performed by this document. On approval, M1 is delivered as a reviewable patch (one page per PR), each validated and stopped for local apply + authoritative CI before the next.
